time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
---

olive oil
2 potato
1 avocado
½ bag parsley
1 packet haloumi/grill cheese
1 courgette
2 tbs milk
½ cup plain flour
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 egg
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
Cut potato into wedges.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil,
season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until tender,
20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, slice avocado in half, scoop out
flesh and roughly chop. Finely chop parsley
(see ingredients).
• Grate haloumi and courgette. Squeeze any
excess moisture out of the courgette using a
paper towel.

TIP: Squeezing out the excess moisture from the
courgette ensures your fritter batter is the right
consistency.

• In a medium bowl, combine haloumi, courgette,
parsley, the milk, plain flour, Aussie spice
blend, the egg and a pinch of salt and pepper.

TIP: Lift out some of the mixture with a spoon. If it's
too wet and doesn't hold its shape, add a little more
flour!

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat
with enough olive oil to coat the base.
• When oil is hot, add heaped tablespoons of
fritter mixture in batches and flatten with a
spatula (3-4 per person).
• Cook until golden, 3-4 minutes each side
(don't flip too early!). Transfer to a paper
towel-lined plate.

TIP: Add extra olive oil between batches as needed.

• In a second medium bowl, combine mixed salad
leaves, avocado and a drizzle of vinegar and
olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide haloumi and courgette fritters, potato
wedges and avocado salad between plates.
• Serve with dill & parsley mayonnaise. Enjoy!